item.description: Donald Trump didn't suddenly decide that transparency is good. He reversed himself on Sunday night and called for House Republicans to vote for the release of the Epstein Files because the vote was happening anyway. Rep. Thomas Massie (R-KY), who filed the discharge petition, predicted that 100 Republicans would vote for it. Those are choices you make when 56% of Americans disapprove of your job performance. Trump's approval among independent voters is also cratering. Meanwhile, he's directed the military on a killing spree of 21 attacks on boats in Latin America. Our military buildup there is at historic levels. Even if this is a distraction strategy, our military has killed 83 people in just two months. The resistance to Trump is more pronounced than ever. Indiana Senate Republican Greg Goode was targeted in a swatting attack tonight after Trump named him as a redistricting opponent. item.title: I cannot wrap my head around WHY it is so important to them-to wipe out our history?! I get evil but the levels and deprivation that they sink to..is mind blowing..
item.description: After all that’s said and done- 10 months of damage they have done- will take YEARS to undo. They’ll be gone with all the money they have stolen from our government while we are left to rebuild what we didn’t destroy. That to me is the most hurtful thing about all this.. But here’s the part that gives me hope: History shows that all communities — especially Black communities — have rebuilt after far worse. Reconstruction. Civil Rights. Every time something oppressive tried to erase progress, people fought back and re-created something even stronger.
